When I took my CPC exam through AAPC, it was an open book exam, but no
dictionary was used.  During the study course for the exam, we were allowed
to make notations in the coding books for certain definitions that would be
important for each body system, but they had to be written on Post-It notes
so they could be moved over to the new books as issued in October of each
year.  I think I scored a 98 on the medical terminology portion of the exam
and don't recall referring to my notes at all.  The proctor looked in
everyone's coding books to make sure nothing other than what was allowed in
class was added into the books we had with us prior to the exam.

The exam was in 3 parts and I only needed to make reference to the coding
books when looking at a report and needing to pull the correct CPT code(s)
and/or modifiers out of the book, which was the hardest part of the exam.

